---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero.astro";

const updated = "June 2026";
---
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="How PalmasMesh.com handles your information. Short version: this is a static informational site, we don't collect personal data, and some product links are affiliate links."
>
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="The fine print"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    lede="The short version: this is a simple informational site run by neighbors. We don't ask for your personal information, and we don't sell anything directly."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap-narrow policy">
      <p class="policy-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>

      <h3>Who we are</h3>
      <p>
        PalmasMesh.com is a community-run informational website about PalmasMesh,
        a neighbor-built Meshtastic radio network in Palmas del Mar, Humacao,
        Puerto Rico. It is not a business, and we don't sell products or services
        through this site.
      </p>

      <h3>What we collect</h3>
      <p>
        Almost nothing. This is a static website — there are no accounts to
        create, no forms that store your details, and no newsletter sign-up. We
        don't ask for your name, email, or any other personal information to read
        these pages.
      </p>
      <p>
        Like most websites, our hosting provider may keep basic, standard server
        logs (for example, the type of request and a general timestamp) to keep
        the site running and secure. We don't use these to identify you, and we
        don't build profiles of visitors.
      </p>

      <h3>Cookies and tracking</h3>
      <p>
        We don't set advertising or tracking cookies, and we don't run
        third-party analytics that follow you around the web. If that ever
        changes, we'll update this page first.
      </p>

      <h3>Affiliate links</h3>
      <p>
        Some links to recommended hardware may be affiliate links. If you click
        one and buy something, PalmasMesh may earn a small commission from that
        retailer — at no extra cost to you. When you click an affiliate link, the
        retailer (for example, the device maker or their store) may set its own
        cookies and apply its own privacy policy, which we don't control.
      </p>
      <p>
        We only recommend gear we'd genuinely point a neighbor toward, whether or
        not it earns a commission. Any commission helps cover the cost of running
        the network and this site.
      </p>

      <h3>Links to other sites</h3>
      <p>
        This site links out to manufacturers, stores, the Meshtastic project, and
        community groups. Once you follow a link off PalmasMesh.com, you're
        subject to that site's own privacy practices. We'd encourage you to read
        their policies if you're concerned about how they handle your data.
      </p>

      <h3>Children</h3>
      <p>
        This is a general-audience informational site and isn't directed at
        children. We don't knowingly collect information from anyone.
      </p>

      <h3>Changes to this policy</h3>
      <p>
        If we change how the site works in a way that affects this policy, we'll
        update the text here and change the "last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h3>Questions</h3>
      <p>
        If you have a question about this policy or the network, reach out through
        the "Meshtastic Puerto Rico" group on Facebook or ask a neighbor who's
        already on the mesh.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .policy h3 {
      margin-top: 2rem;
      color: var(--ink);
    }
    .policy h3:first-of-type { margin-top: 0; }
    .policy-updated {
      font-family: var(--mono);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--ink-soft);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
  </style>
</Base>
